&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Views" /><category term="Aerial" /><summary type="html">The Tennoji/Abeno area of Osaka, looking northwest from the top of the Abeno Harukas tower, the tallest building in Japan. The purple tower, center-right, is the Tsutenkaku Tower of the Shinsekai district. The Osaka Tennoji Park and Zoo is the dark area at the bottom. Abiko-Suji is the street along the left side, crossed by the elevated Hanshin Highway 14, lit in orange. The Yodogawa River makes its way across the top of the picture to the Seto Inland Sea (top left) and the city of Kobe. Below, more photos from Abeno Harukas including Osaka Castle and Shitennoji Temple.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07874-3.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07874-3.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kennin-ji・建仁寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220421/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kennin-ji・建仁寺" /><published>2022-04-21T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-04-21T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kenninji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220421/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
